sentences: In 2007 Hunter founded an independent record label based in Houston, Texas, Feow!

After releasing their debut, Twin-Hand Movement, on Gnomonsong in 2010, Lower Dens were one of the first bands signed to the Ribbon Music label and released their second album, Nootropics, on Ribbon in 2012.

Hunter is the inspiration for several characters in the stories of J.M. Appel, including providing the basis for Maggie in the novella Fallout (2010).
In 2005, Hunter accompanied Meadows, Lights, and Mouth of Leaves on their Summer of Golden Blood tour throughout the South.
In 2006, Hunter performed at North East Sticks Together.
In 2019, Hunter created a special playlist for Billboards Summer of Pride event.

In 2014, Hunter came out as gender fluid (or non-binary), as well being neither gay nor straight, stating that they "feel extremely fortunate in that I truly don’t give a fuck when it comes to the gender of the person I’m dating".
In August 2019, an article by Billboard.com stated that Hunter preferred he/him pronouns.
In 2021 Hunter revealed he'd been diagnosed as having autism and ADHD.
